i know my mans dr seuss was a political satirist before he was a children author so i wouldnt put it past him to depict such broad metaphysical things in a childrens book
now, i ask you to remember how the other "gods" planned to boil horton in beezle nut oil. this represents the struggle between religions/gods and religious "superiority"
well, much like Earth, i assume the Whos have diverse people, the grinch being one of them. i imagine horton has limited intervention powers and allowed the grinchs story to unfold as it would
an interesting point that arose: the grinch. the grinch steals christmas from Whoville in another seuss story but how does that play in to horton?
the kangaroo is a vindicitve god to foil horton. maisy is a childish and aloof god, so on and so forth.

you may ask: what about the other animals in the jungle of nool, all the birds and the kangaroo that is oh so cruel (channeling my inner dr seuss)? well, those animals are other gods. the Whos have an entire pantheon!
i think that establishes that horton could be a god to the Whos. BUT WAIT THERES MORE!
furthermore, the Whos live in fear because "any gust of wind" can ruin their lives, much like unforseen circumstances can ruin human lives
an aside about the Whos: in some adaptations, the Whos are trying to reach the mystical paradise, the name of which i am forgetting, and ask horton to help them reach the paradise

jojo calls out to horton, a force she cannot see and at first is hesitant to believe is real. the other Whos are skeptical of hortons existence until their survival depends on horton, at which point all the Whos call out to him
horton effectively has omnipotent control over the "world" of Whoville since he carries around the clover/galaxy and protects it from harm- much like a benevolent god would do

we all know that horton hears this Who coming from a dust speck upon a clover. the dust speck represents a world, much like our own Earth. the clover represents something like a galaxy, and the jungle of nool (hortons home) is the universe
